Have made this 3 times in the last 6 weeks (for different groups of people!). Delicious - big hit - lemon zest mingled with olive oil makes it. Used Vidalia onion and sweet grape tomatoes.

Rating: 4
I've served this over and over, and have passed on the recipe to many. One change that makes a difference is to marinate the veggies in the dressing for a few hours, then arrange them on the platter just before serving. The marinating takes the sharpness out of sometimes strong onions. Red onion is good too.

Rating: 4
I made this the other night to rave reviews from my family. I'd made a few changes based on other reviews: I roasted both a yellow and red pepper, used a red onion slivered over the top of the salad,and added marinated mushrooms. I also used homegrown cukes. Delicious! Will make again!

Rating: 2
I was medium on this. I made it in Feb., so that may have made a difference, but I used baby cucumbers and tomatos, and both had a good flavor to me. Frozen artichokes (the kind I bought) didn't add much. Dressing wasn't that great- oregano didn't come through, and usually they say dried is better than fresh. For this, I would try fresh. Also added some pita chip croutons. Overall, kind of tasty, but nothing special.

