Rating: 4
This was an awesome salad. I reduced the onion to about 1 c. I used a tapenade in place of the kalamata olives. Also reduced the olive oil to 1/2 c (8 tbsp). Took previous reviewer suggestion and used marinated artichokes in place of the frozen. Will make this salad again. Would be perfect in the summertime to go with anything bbq.

Rating: 4
Incredible salad. I strongly reccommend that you skip the frozen artichoke and use marinated artichoke hearts. Great with marinated leg of lamb.

Rating: 4
Since I wasn't making this for company, I just sliced everything in bite-size pieces and tossed in a bowl with the dressing and it still made an impressive salad and tasted great. I think the key is the lemon zest - it perks up the salad, but isn't overpowering.

Rating: 3
This recipe is easy, tasty, and very appealing visually. I used marinated artichoke hearts (and drained off the marinade). I used a red onion and a yellow pepper for visual diversity. I used a garlic basil feta for extra flavor. Impressive.